				<li id="16661771" class="cmnt-root" data="11" data-d="1651350985000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578591/Honed-Bolt" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 Apr 2022 16:36</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16661771" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Just so onlookers are on the same page; There are many, many &quot;bugged&quot; incantation combos. They are performed with arbitrary spells in an arbitrary order (there is pretty much zero logic to any of them other than their animation cancelling effects) but almost universally include a running/walking/rolling/BHS cast animation - or several. Performing the combo in the correct order will completely cancel certain casting animations, making the spells&apos; effects go off both instantaneously and simultaneously. This spell is part of several of those combos. It&apos;s hard to imagine these specific combos are working as intended, however...<br/><br/>There are tons of bugs and glitches and unintended interactions in this game. Like, a whole bunch. They get patched based on severity, and whined about based on severity. Nobody cares that Cold Antspur +5 still has 75 Scarlet Rot build-up for some unknown reason, but people (rightfully) cared about Carian Retaliation + Glintstone Scrap invisible one-shots up until it was patched. Nobody cares that Fire&apos;s Deadly Sin still possesses its broken interaction with Bloodflame because it sucks compared to what people were doing with Death Blight before it was patched.<br/><br/>Whether or not you choose to employ any of these broken interactions is ultimately up to you. More people abusing them may in some indirect way contribute to them getting patched. Whether you think they are more or less fair than RoB/MV spammers or whatever flavour the &quot;legit&quot; cheese of the day is, is up to you. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16661771" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16661771" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>12</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16661771"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16661771" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16661771"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16653991" class="cmnt-root" data="16" data-d="1651114403000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578591/Honed-Bolt" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Apr 2022 22:53</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16653991" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Cintrary to what many people claim, It isn&apos;t bugged with bestial sling if used normally. Bestial sling is supposed to shorten the next cast&apos;s startup animation.<br/><br/>However, like many spells, it is bugged if you use running, rolling, or double bestial sling before it. Much like Theodorix&apos;s Magma, it completely skips the casting animation rather than shorten it. By checking the animation data, there is actually an error in the code that&apos;s supposed to shorten the cast, but instead skips it completely.<br/><br/>I believe I&apos;ve been objective enough. As for my opinion, I see it too much in duels. Because it&apos;s good, admittedly. Still, a bug is a bug. Take from that what you will.<br/><br/>This was tested in Patch 1.0.4 at 25 dex with Radagon&apos;s Icon, and at 10 dex with no talismans. Casting speed does not affect the bugged casts whatsoever.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16653991" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16653991" class="cmt-reply pull-rig